parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction or fail, leading to safety risks, inconvenience, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Headlights not working
dashboard lights and gauges malfunctioning
power windows and door locks not functioning
airbag light staying on
electrical burning smell
and unexpected restarting of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: Key getting stuck in the ignition switch
vehicle not starting
ignition switch not turning off
and electrical burning smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power or not shift properly, leading to safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling
loss of power
and transmission not shifting properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Inlet Valve Failure and Fuel Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank inlet valve can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and accidents, posing a significant risk to the safety of the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Strong fuel odor
fuel leaks
fuel gauge malfunctions
check engine light illumination
and stalling or difficulty starting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle stalls on a busy highway or in a hazardous location.
symptoms: Inaccurate fuel level readings
fuel gauge stuck on full or empty
and difficulty determining the actual fuel level.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause various safety issues, including stalling, loss of power, and failure of critical systems, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Inaccurate or malfunctioning speedometer
malfunctioning rearview mirrors
and malfunctioning seat controls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, become stuck in gear, or refuse to shift, leading to accidents, loss of control, or stranding.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or refuses to shift gears
slips out of gear
or becomes stuck in gear; the transmission makes unusual noises or leaks fluid.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the four-wheel drive system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, become stuck, or lose control, leading to accidents or stranding.
symptoms: The four-wheel drive system fails to engage or disengage
the vehicle becomes stuck or loses traction
the service four-wheel drive light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fan clutch can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: The fan clutch makes a loud noise
the fan clutch fails to engage or disengage
the engine overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to lose power, become stuck, or lose control, leading to accidents or stranding.
symptoms: The transfer case fails to engage or disengage
the vehicle becomes stuck or loses traction
the service four-wheel drive light illuminates on the dashboard.
